{
  "texts": [
    "Training instances with negative influence are called opponents or inhibitory examples (Koh & Liang, 2017; Yeh et al., 2018).",
    "Highly expressive, overparameterized models remain functionally black boxes (Koh & Liang, 2017).",
    "Understanding why a model behaves in a specific way remains a significant challenge (Belle & Papantonis, 2021), and the inclusion or removal of even a single training instance can drastically change a trained model's behavior (Rousseeuw, 1994; Black & Fredrikson, 2021).",
    "In the worst case, quantifying one training instance's influence may require repeating all of training.",
    "Since measuring influence exactly may be intractable or unnecessary, influence estimators-which only approximate the true influence-are commonly used in practice."
  ]
}